OL,3,C'High' alert for air pollution issued
OL,4,Cas 'hottest day of the year' expected
OL,6,FLondoners have been advised to switch
OL,7,Fvehicle engines off when stopped and
OL,8,Favoid burning wood or garden waste.
OL,10,FThe Deputy Mayor of Environment and
OL,11,FEnergy, Mete Coban said: "London's
OL,12,Ftoxic air is responsible for around
OL,13,F4,000 premature deaths in the capital
OL,14,Feach year, which is why the Mayor has
OL,15,Fdone everything in his power to tackle
OL,16,Fit.
